Detailed Description

template<class T>
class Sylph::Core::Iterator< T >

Iterator provides a transparant interface for iterating over collections.

Each Iterable should have a specific implementation of this class. In case a certain method cannot be implemented (e.g. previous() when a collection does not support reverse iteration) it should throw an UnsupportedOperationException.

This class is used implicitly by sforeach(), and therefore a correct implementation of it is necessary if you want to use sforeach().
